{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9f4abbbc-6e25-408b-a8e3-42f54dac37b0","content":"This is a well-known MTP behavioral difference. **Exit code 8** means \"no tests were discovered.\" VSTest returned 0 in this case; MTP treats it as an error by default.\n\n**Fix:** Tell MTP to ignore exit code 8 by setting an environment variable or a project property.\n\n**Option 1 — In your `.csproj`** (recommended, permanent fix):","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013obQMnzEPhLktgqkDAMEmA","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-54f1ec466ff04901841fd6a12592bd0d/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n    <!-- Treat zero-test assemblies as success (matches VSTest behavior) -->\n    <TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>--ignore-exit-code 8</TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-54f1ec466ff04901841fd6a12592bd0d/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"e25d6c98-8066-41ee-9d7a-5a219ed29cfa","outputTokens":344,"requestId":"1BCC:13C87:AC56F4:C41A5C:6A03CF17"},"id":"b76a449d-54ea-4cf6-82ee-cd5ac9968bd3","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:08:45.555Z","parentId":"7f1061d5-725f-4ce6-b327-83ee95ef7791"}
